cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the energy and coverage efficiency of small-cell networks in fifth-generation cellular networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of the BS-switch-off strategy in terms of energy and coverage efficiency. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a strategy for saving energy consumption in small-cell networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper analyses the massive multi-input-multi-output system in small-cell networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss security concerns related to the BS-switch-off strategy.
